
Overview of noun terror

The noun terror has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (11) panic, terror, affright -- (an overwhelming feeling of fear and anxiety)
2. (1) terror, scourge, threat -- (a person who inspires fear or dread; "he was the terror of the neighborhood")
3. terror, brat, little terror, holy terror -- (a very troublesome child)
4. terror -- (the use of extreme fear in order to coerce people (especially for political reasons); "he used terror to make them confess")
